// This custom hook keeps all month-range state in one reusable place.

// It uses mutiple useState calls to store each piece of state separately, which is a common React pattern.

// For example, the start month and end month are stored in separate state variables, 
// and the available month bounds are also stored separately.

// Please note these file has been deprecated in favour of useChartDateRange.jsx ,
// which uses a single useReducer call to manage all related state together.
// The advantage of the new approach is that all state updates are grouped into named actions,
// which can be easier to maintain in larger apps.


